{"name": "nanobind", "metadata": {"name": "nanobind", "version": "2.2.0", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Programming Language :: C++", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "nanobind: tiny and efficient C++/Python bindings", "upload_time": 1727931960}, "documentation": ["![nanobind logo](\nhttps://github.com/wjakob/nanobind/raw/master/docs/images/logo.jpg?raw=True)\n\n_nanobind_ is a small binding library that exposes C++ types in Python and\nvice versa. It is reminiscent of\n[Boost.Python](https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_64_0/libs/python/doc/html)\nand [pybind11](http://github.com/pybind/pybind11) and uses near-identical\nsyntax. In contrast to these existing tools, nanobind is more efficient:\nbindings compile in a shorter amount of time, produce smaller binaries, and\nhave better runtime performance.\n\nMore concretely,\n[benchmarks](https://nanobind.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmark.html) show up\nto **~4\u00d7 faster** compile time, **~5\u00d7 smaller** binaries, and **~10\u00d7 lower**\nruntime overheads compared to pybind11. nanobind also outperforms Cython in\nimportant metrics (**3-12\u00d7** binary size reduction, **1.6-4\u00d7** compilation time\nreduction, similar runtime performance).\n\nPlease see the following links for tutorial and reference documentation in\n[HTML](https://nanobind.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) and\n[PDF](https://nanobind.readthedocs.io/_/downloads/en/latest/pdf/) formats.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "nanobind", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "nanobind.include_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.cmake_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "nanobind.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "nanobind.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "nanobind.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "nanobind.cmake_dir", "xref": {"fqname": "nanobind.cmake_dir", "project": null}}, {"name": "nanobind.include_dir", "xref": {"fqname": "nanobind.include_dir", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "nanobind.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "nanobind.__main__.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen", "documentation": ["stubgen.py: nanobind stub generation tool\n\nThis file provides both an API (`nanobind.stubgen.StubGen`) and a command\nline interface to generate stubs for nanobind extensions.\n\nTo generate stubs on the command line, invoke the stub generator with a module\nname, which will place the newly generated `.pyi` file directly into the\nmodule folder.\n\n`` `\npython -m nanobind.stubgen <module name>\n` ``\n\nSpecify `-o <filename>` or `-O <path>` to redirect the output somewhere\nelse in case this is not desired.\n\nTo programmatically generate stubs, construct an instance of the `StubGen`\nclass and repeatedly call `.put()` to register modules or contents within the\nmodules (specific methods, classes, etc.). Afterwards, the `.get()` method\nreturns a string containing the stub declarations.\n\n\\`\nfrom nanobind.stubgen import StubGen\nimport my_module\n\nsg = StubGen()\nsg.put(my_module)\nprint(sg.get())&#10;\n\n# Internals:\n\nThe implementation of stubgen performs a DFS traversal of the loaded module and\ndirectly generates the stub in lockstep. There are no ASTs or other\nintermediate data structures to keep things as simple as possible. Every kind\nof object that could be encountered (functions, properties, values, types) has\na corresponding `put_..` method, along with the main `put()` entry point\nthat dispatches to the others as appropriate.\n\nInternally, stub generation involves two potentially complex steps: converting\nnanobind overload chains into <mailto:'@overload>' declarations that can be understood\nby the 'typing' module, and turning default values back into Python\nexpressions. To make both steps well-defined, the implementation relies on an\ninternal `__nb_signature__` property that nanobind functions expose\nspecifically to simplify stub generation.\n\n(Note that for now, the StubGen API is considered experimental and not subject\n\n: to the semantic versioning policy used by the nanobind project.)\n", "!/usr/bin/env python3", "pyright: strict"], "functions": [{"name": "nanobind.stubgen.parse_options", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "argparse.Namespace", "xref": {"fqname": "argparse.Namespace", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.load_pattern_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fname", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "ReplacePattern", "xref": {"fqname": "nanobind.stubgen.ReplacePattern", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Load a pattern file from disk and return a list of pattern instances that\nincludes precompiled versions of all of the contained regular expressions."]}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "args", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "nanobind.stubgen.typing_extensions", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.SKIP_LIST", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.ImportDict", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.PackagesDict", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NbSignature", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NbFunctionSignature", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NbGetterSetterSignature", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NamedObject", "bases": ["Protocol"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NamedObject.__module__", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NamedObject.__name__", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Typing protocol representing an object with __name__ and __module__ members"]}, {"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NbFunction", "bases": ["Protocol"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "nanobind.stubgen.NbFunction.__module__", "type": {"name": "Literal", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Literal", "